}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#Event",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Event describing a development involving one or more resources at a given time."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Un événément décrit une évolution impliquant une ou plusieurs ressources à un instant donné."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Event"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Événément"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#Landmark",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#LandmarkRelation",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Il s'agit d'une relation qui représente un lien existant entre un ou plusieurs repères.\r\n    Ces relations peuvent prendre diverses formes, notamment :\r\n    - des relations géographiques, par exemple lorsqu'un point de repère est situé à l'angle de deux autres points de repère ;\r\n    - des relations hiérarchiques, par exemple lorsqu'un point de repère est la capitale d'une autre entité administrative ;\r\n    - d'autres relations spécifiques."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "It is a relation that represents a relation existing between one or more landmarks.\r\n    Such relations may take various forms, including:\r\n    - geographic relations, for example when a landmark is located at the corner of two other landmarks;\r\n    - hierarchical relations, for example when a landmark is the capital of another administrative entity;\r\n    - as well as other domain-specific or contextual relations depending on the application needs.\r\n    "
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Landmark relation"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Relation entre repères"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#LandmarkType",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "A type of landmark is a category that allows classifying the different types of landmarks."
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Un type de repère est une catégorie qui permet de classer les différents types de repères."
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Type de repère"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Type of landmark"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#Concept"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#hasTrace",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Describes that an element has another element as its trace"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Décrit qu'un élément a pour trace un autre élément"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "a pour trace"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "has trace"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#isTraceOf",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty" ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment" : [ {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Describes that an element is the trace of another element"
  }, {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Décrit qu'un élément est la trace d'un autre élément"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "est une trace de"
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "is trace of"
  } ],
  "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf" : [ {
    "@id" : "https://w3id.org/PeGazUs#hasTrace"
  } ]
}, {
  "@id" : "https://w3id.org/tabulae#",
  "@type" : [ "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology", "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#NamedIndividual" ],
  "http://creativecommons.org/ns#license" : [ {
    "@id" : "http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/"
  }, {
    "@id" : "http://opendatacommons.org/licenses/by/"
  }, {
    "@id" : "http://www.data.gouv.fr/Licence-Ouverte-Open-Licence"
  } ],
  "http://purl.org/dc/terms/abstract" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "L'ontologie TABULAE est une extension de l'ontologie PeGazUs dédiée à la représentation des informations relatives aux parcelles contenues dans les documents du cadastre ancien français (XIXe siècle). Elle permet de décrire les parcelles (Plot), leurs contribuables (Taxpayer), leur nature d'occupation du sol (Nature, avec plus de 150 valeurs contrôlées), ainsi que les événements et changements qui affectent ces parcelles au fil du temps. Leur évolution est décrite à l'échelle des attributs. L'ontologie modélise également les sources documentaires mobilisées (matrices cadastrales, états de sections, plans parcellaires) et intègre un support pour la classification automatique et la reconnaissance d'entités nommées dans les documents numérisés (anclass, NamedEntity). Elle s'appuie sur les ontologies PeGazUs, RiC-O, SKOS et PROV-O."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "L'ontology TABULAE is an extension of the PeGazUs vocabulary dedicated to the representation of information contained in the French 19th-century land registry documents. It enables the description of land plots, their taxpayers, their nature (with over 150 controlled values), and the changes and events affecting these plots over time. Their evolution is described at the attribute level. The ontology also models the sources involved (mutation registers, section registers, cadastral index maps) and provides support for automatic classification and named entity recognition in digitised documents (anclass, NamedEntity). It builds on the PeGazUs, RiC-O, SKOS and PROV-O ontologies."
  } ],
  "http://purl.org/dc/terms/contributor" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid1"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid3"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid5"
  }, {
    "@id" : "_:genid7"
  } ],
  "http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator" : [ {
    "@id" : "_:genid9"
  } ],
  "http://purl.org/dc/terms/description" : [ {
    "@language" : "fr",
    "@value" : "Ontologie pour décrire les informations sur les parcelles, et les entités liées, présentes dans le cadastre ancien. Extension de l'ontologie PeGaZus."
  }, {
    "@language" : "en",
    "@value" : "Ontology to describe the information about land plots and associated entities evocated in the old land registry documents. Extension of the PeGazUs ontology."
  } ],
  "http://purl.org/dc/terms/issued" : [ {
    "@type" : "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date",
    "@value" : "2024-01-24"
  } ],
